pullRequest.body:
Move the definition of `algebraicClosure` into a separated file (mimicing `seperableClosure` in file FieldTheory.SeperableClosure). Add APIs for `algebraicClosure`. Most are copied api's from `separableClosure`. Show that every algebraic intermediate extension is contained in the algebraic closure.

One generic observation, not sure if it's something we should do:
We could also define `IntermediateField.algebraicClosure` which takes an intermediate field `E/K/F`, and sends it to `E/L/F`, where `L` is the algebraic closure of `K` in `F`.
The current definition would then be the special case `algebraicClosure \bot`.
But if we don't have a use case for this, maybe we should ignore it :smile:

```suggestion
The *relative algebraic closure* of a field `F` in a field extension `E`,
also called the *maximal algebraic subextension* of `E / F`,
is defined to be the subalgebra `integralClosure F E`
upgraded to an intermediate field (since `F` and `E` are both fields).
This is exactly the intermediate field of `E / F` consisting of all integral/algebraic elements.
```
Thanks!
Should this live in the root namespace? Then the name seems ambiguous, because it might also be an absolute algebraic closure...

Note that this def is moved, not renamed.
We already use lowercase [separableClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure) for the relative one and uppercase [SeparableClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#SeparableClosure) for the absolute one. The absolute algebraic closure is uppercased [AlgebraicClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsAlgClosed/AlgebraicClosure.html#AlgebraicClosure).

I think as @alreadydone said, this is aligned with the current naming convention. See also [normalClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/NormalClosure.html#normalClosure) . @jcommelin  Do you suggest we should change all [separableClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure), algebraicClosure and [normalClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/NormalClosure.html#normalClosure) into `IntermediateField.fooClosure` version? I would be happy to do this in another PR if necessary.

```suggestion
variable {K L : Type*} [Field K] [Field L] [Algebra K L]
```

Let's add a bit of whitespace, to indicate the namespace applies to many declarations instead of just the next one.
```suggestion
namespace algebraicClosure

```
Thank you!

As above:
```suggestion
namespace algebraicClosure

```
Sure!

```suggestion
subextensions (this means that it is purely transcendental),
```

```suggestion
  simpa only [mem_algebraicClosure_iff, IsAlgebraic, ne_eq, ← aeval_algebraMap_eq_zero_iff E,
    Algebra.id.map_eq_id, RingHom.id_apply, IntermediateField.algebraMap_apply] using hs ⟨x, h⟩
```

```suggestion
namespace algebraicClosure

```
